overview: There are still some clean places on earth, but for how long? Broome is located in the far remote Kimberley region, which is the last great Wilderness of Australia. This is where Colin Barnett, Premier of Western Australia, and the multibillionair oil & gas company, Woodside, decided to settle the second largest LNG precinct of the planet. Broome citizens and the traditional custodians of the land - the Goolaraboloo - united together to protect what is priceless to them...
title: Heritage Fight
